correctness.rationale: Largely incorrect and schema-violating with many untraceable values. Key issues: (1) ALD method misassigned: pO and WpO processes are labeled TALD but should be PEALD; only the H2O (W) process is thermal. (2) Pressure is not reported in the article; a fabricated 1.0 Torr is used and unit violates schema (requires MilliM_HG). (3) Growth-per-cycle unit violates schema (used NanoM; schema requires ANGSTROM). (4) Dosing and purge time units violate schema (used SEC; schema requires MilliSEC). (5) WpO dosing incomplete: only a single co-reactant time (15 s) is given; article specifies H2O 15 s followed by O2 plasma 8 s (both should be captured). (6) For the H2O process, plasmaPower is set to null (schema expects an object or omission). (7) Flow rates (100 sccm) are not reported anywhere; all flow values are fabricated. (8) Numerous material/device properties are fabricated or use wrong units/methods: refractive index, absorption coefficient (unit must be UNITLESS per schema), band gap measured by UV–Vis (not reported), electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, mobility), uniformity, conformality, roughness (AFM), and film density (uses GM-PER-CM3 instead of schema’s GM-PER-DeciM3 and value doesn’t match article’s ~5.1–5.2 g/cm3 via HR-RBS). (9) Film composition: ‘elementalConcentration 50% by XPS’ is not reported; only O/Zn ~1 (RBS) and impurity trends (SIMS) are given. (10) OtherAspects include unsupported claims (precursor “not pyrophoric,” filmStability, reproducibility). Correct items include temperature (200 °C), Ar carrier/purge gases and 15 s purge, precursor/co-reactant choices, and pulse times and GPCs for pO and W processes; film thicknesses and linear growth/no nucleation delay are consistent. To correct: fix ALD method (PEALD for pO and WpO), remove or source pressure and use required unit, convert GPC to Å/cycle, convert times to ms, add both co-reactant times for WpO, omit plasmaPower for W, remove fabricated flow/material/device data or replace with reported values (e.g., O/Zn≈1 by RBS; densities ~5.1–5.2 g/cm3), and use schema-compliant units throughout.

completeness.rationale: Although the three distinct ZnO ALD processes (O2 plasma, H2O, and H2O→O2 plasma) are recognized and some key values (GPC, cycles, film thickness, substrate, temperature, purge time, carrier/purge gas, plasma power=100 W where applicable) align with the article, the extraction has numerous schema and traceability issues and several inaccuracies: (1) ALD method mislabeling: the pO and WpO processes are marked as TALD instead of PEALD. (2) Schema unit violations: dosingTime and purgeTime use SEC instead of required MilliSEC; growthPerCycle uses NanoM instead of ANGSTROM; pressure uses Torr instead of required MilliM_HG; filmDensity uses GM-PER-CM3 instead of GM-PER-DeciM3; optical absorption uses PER-NanoM whereas schema expects UNITLESS for the specified quantity kinds. (3) Invalid/nullable field: plasmaPower is set to None for the H2O-only process, violating the object type (should be omitted). (4) Missing critical dosing detail for WpO: the adopted O2 plasma co-reactant pulse of 8 s is not represented in dosingTime (only the 15 s H2O pulse is given). (5) Unsourced or fabricated values: reactor pressure (1 Torr), all flow rates, optical properties (n, absorption), electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, mobility), uniformity, conformality, roughness, and XRR-based film density (5.6 g/cm3) are not reported in the article (article reports density ≈5.1–5.2 g/cm3 from HR-RBS + thickness, not XRR). (6) Film composition: atomic ratio 1:1 via RBS is consistent qualitatively, but the elemental concentration (50% by XPS) is not provided in the paper and the technique differs (article used HR-RBS and SIMS). (7) Safety statement (“not pyrophoric”) is not explicitly stated for this precursor. (8) Important reported crystallographic orientations [(002) for H2O; (103) for O2 plasma; intermediate for WpO] are not captured in the crystallinity field. To improve: correct ALD methods (PEALD for pO and WpO), remove None values, fix all units to match schema (ms, Å, mmHg, g/dm3), add the 8 s O2 plasma dose for WpO, remove or leave out-of-scope properties not reported (optical, electrical, uniformity, conformality, flow rates, pressure) rather than fabricate, set film density to ~5.1–5.2 g/cm3 with characterization method consistent with the article, and include the reported XRD orientations in the crystallinity description.
